\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. E. beketowii} Schmalh., {\i Fl. Sred. Juz. Ross. }{\b 1}: 198 (1895). Perennial; stems 15-30 cm. Leaves c. 10 cm, bipinnate, with narrowly linear segments, greyish with numerous appressed, glandular hairs; intercalary leaflets present. Umbel with 5-15 flowers. Sepals c. 9 mm; petals c. 8 mm, lilac. Mericarps c. 7 mm; beak 30-40 mm.{\i  Rocky and gravelly places. • S.E. Ukraine} ({\i Kal'mius and Kal'cik valleys, near Zdanov}). Rs (W).
\par

