\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. E. rodiei} (Br.-Bl.) Poirion,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  74}: 14 (1967) ({\i E. petraeum} subsp.{\i  rodiei }Br.-Bl.). Acaulescent perennial. Leaves 3-5 cm, ovate, long-petiolate, subglabrous, pinnate, with intercalary leaflets; leaflets deeply pinnatisect; ultimate segments linear, entire. Peduncles 8-20 cm. Umbels with 2-8(-10) flowers; bracts long-acuminate. Sepals 9-11 mm; petals 15-20 mm, bright pink. Mericarps 7-8 mm, with ascending, pale brown hairs; apical pits eglandular, without a furrow at the base. Beak 30-35 mm.{\i  Fissures in dolomite rock. • S.E. France} ({\i N.W. of Grasse}). Ga.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Some variants of {\b 23}({\b a}) from shaded situations resemble {\b 24}, but their petals are always smaller and their leaves hairier.
