\pard\f0\fs28  A very variable and difficult complex. Within the compass of the species as here delimited over 30 binomials have been proposed for European plants (omitting those of A. Jordan)but the delimitation of these supposed species has been attempted if at all, with reference only to immediately adjacent populations. The only recent attempt to survey the field more widely is that of Litardière in Briquet,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Corse}{\b  2}({\b 2}): 28-35 (1936), and we follow here his taxonomic scheme, subject to nomenclatural revisions suggested by Guittonneau,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr}.
